You will spawn in a world beside a village and in front of the commands. Climb the ladder and pull the lever to start. title: ON/OFF Switch
briefDescription: This is a small map which adds the ON/OFF Switch featured in Super Mario Maker 2. It uses command blocks, redstone, and some maps to ...

crawledImageUrls.text:
This is a small map which adds the ON/OFF Switch featured in Super Mario Maker 2. It uses command blocks, redstone, and some maps to make it as close to the one from the real game. The only down side is that this is not an add-on so you can?t use it in you?re own world, but other than that, it works great!
When you get in the world you will see a barrel with a sign above it labled ?you need:? and inside of the barrel you will find everything you need in order to get the ON/OFF Switch block started.
?FIRST activate all the command blocks by flipping the lever labled ?On/Off lever? After you grab all the items from the barrel you should have everything that you need. When you place down an armor stand and name it ?switch? by using a name tag, the armor stand will become invisible and an ON/OFF Switch block should appear. Keep in mind that if you break the armor stand under the ON/OFF Switch block, it will not work
?NEXT you can spawn chickens or parrots to be the placeholders for the red/blue blocks that appear when you hit the switch block (they float in the air). If you misplace a block (chicken or parrot) then you can use the ?Break Blocks? (diamond sword) found in the barrel to ?break the blocks?
-Chickens will have blue concrete blocks appear in front of them when the switch block is ?OFF?
-Parrots will have red concrete blocks appear in front of them when the switch block is ?ON?

Do you consider yourself a true Whovian (also known as a Doctor Who fan)? If that?s the case then you definitely have to download this map and give it a try in-game. The map features many of the control rooms and other TARDIS areas and all of them are based on the ones in the Doctor Who TV show. You?ll start out in the Overworld at a police box and from there you can access the TARDIS!
Creator: MicroJP, Twitter Account, YouTube Channel
All of the rooms are connected by corridors so you can easily go from one to another without leaving the building.

Finally after many months, the Working PlayStation 4 -the next addition to the ?working? series- is available for download! Have you ever wanted to know what is would feel like to play on a PS4 in Minecraft? Well this map is just right for you!
Click below to see a trailer for the map (it?s amazing) or continue reading for a description of the map:
This map is a recreation of a PlayStation 4 in Minecraft. It uses redstone and a lot of command blocks that allow you to play with and access a variety of different features.
Some of those features include: Minecraft, Sonic Mania, the ability to take up to 20 screenshots and save them to a capture gallery, and MUCH more!

title: Redstone Alternatives
briefDescription: This world explains a way people used mechanisms in MCPE before Redstone was added in 0.13.0. This uses signs, cacti, sand and more to show you ...

crawledImageUrls.text:
This world explains a way people used mechanisms in MCPE before Redstone was added in 0.13.0. This uses signs, cacti, sand and more to show you Rube Goldberg-style mechanisms without Redstone. If you need one-time-use doors, are nostalgic, or want to learn about this, this is the map for you!
Do you want to build doors you can only use for one time? Do you want to learn about the history of MCPE? Are you just simply nostalgic? Then this map?s for you! Simple explaination of history: People who played MCPE from release to 0.13.0 didn?t have proper Redstone, so they innovated and created these alternatives. These Rube Goldberg machines use signs, sand, cacti, and more to create mechanisms!

title: Souls (BedWars Mingame)
briefDescription: This is a exiting action packed map full of fun! Play with up to 4 friends in a P.V.P. fight to the death! This ...

crawledImageUrls.text: This is a exiting action packed map full of fun! Play with up to 4 friends in a P.V.P. fight to the death! This map is a remade version of bed wars with a twist; if your soul dies, you do too!!!

There are two game modes in the map souls. (Switchable in lobby) Chaos and normal modes. In normal mode you acquire normal gear. (Iron gear) In Chaos mode you acquire extreme gear. (Diamond Gear) Game modes also impact the upgrades you get from emeralds.
